{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"SCENARIO 6 (semantic conflict) PASS live — THE critical AC: 'Verified=-1 blocking submit on an empty auto-merge diff'. Construction: base module _e2e_s6_base_<stamp> landed on main (change 271); a PYTEST TEST importing it landed on dedicated branch feature/e2e-s6-<stamp> (change 273, bot-reviewed); main DELETED the base module (change 275, net-zero on main); then the --no-ff merge of the dedicated branch into main = change 276 (https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/c/rebar/+/276). RESULT: auto-merge delta = /MERGE_LIST only (clean merge, EMPTY author delta) -> LLM-Review=+1 PASSES (nothing to review); CI RED on the merged tree (pytest collection ImportError: the test imports the now-deleted module) -> Verified=-1; Verified SR UNSATISFIED -> submit BLOCKED. Two-vote complementarity proven: the review bot reviews the (empty) author delta while CI tests the full merged tree and catches the semantic break. Note: needed a pytest-collected test (not a plain module) because mypy has ignore_missing_imports=true, so only pytest's real import surfaces the break. Merge abandoned + dedicated branch torn down in cleanup."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783146811770519001,"uuid":"0e2cc170-ce9b-4dbb-b9be-7129e96a580c"}